U.S. Energy Secretary Dan Brouillette does not believe the ultimate impact of China’s fast-spreading coronavirus is a cause for concern for markets.Bouillette discussed virus’ impact on OPEC and the global market in an exclusive with CNBC’s Hadley Gamble at the Munich Security Conference. “We have to put together very, very tough measures to contain the virus and if we do that effectively then I think you’ll see the markets bounce back and you’ll see the economies continue to grow,” he said.Story: https://cnb.cx/2Soh19s_____________________________Subscribe to CNBC International TV: http://cnb.cx/2wAkfMv

